The '''Council of Lords''', also known as the '''Noble council''', was the legislative body of the [[Onderon/Legends|Onderonian]] government during the time of the [[First Jedi Purge]]. As of [[3951 BBY]], among its ranks were included [[Lord/Legends|Lord]] [[Dashel]], and some time prior to that, the late husband of [[Terlyn]], who had attempted to [[Assassin/Legends|assassinate]] [[General/Legends|General]] [[Vaklu]]. That same [[Standard year/Legends|year]], they debated the issue of Onderon seceding from the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]], which [[Queen/Legends|Queen]] [[Talia (Onderon)|Talia]] opposed, but Vaklu supported.

In [[3627 BBY]], the council was supportive of the Galactic Republic during [[King/Legends|King]] [[Regalun Petryph]]'s political crisis.

==Behind the scenes==
The Council of Lords is mentioned briefly in several "news holograms" that the player, as the [[Meetra Surik|Jedi Exile]], can access while in [[Iziz/Legends|Iziz]].

